author: Barry Horn
title: Football town: More in Dallas watched 2 non-Cowboys NFL games than Rangers' AL West clincher
text:
The Cowboys played to their largest hometown television audience of the season in Sunday night's 26-20 loss to the New Orleans Saints.
The game earned a 37.3 rating for KXAS (Channel 5). That means 37.3 percent of all D-FW homes with television sets tuned in. That's 987,107 homes that tuned in to the thrill of a tie and the agony of an overtime defeat.
The Cowboys loss to the Saints dominated the local ratings on a day the Rangers clinched the American League West title with a commanding 9-2 victory over the Los Angeles Angels in a game that was close as late as the seventh inning. The Rangers-Angels on Fox Sports Southwest and TBS scored a 7.0, a number that could be updated later Monday. The 7.0 translates into 185,248 happy homes.
The power of the NFL in Dallas-Fort Worth on television was on display in the ratings. Here's a Sunday rundown;
Cowboys-Saints: 37.3
Packers-49ers: 12.8
Giants-Bills: 9.3
Rangers-Angels FSSW & TBS: 7.0
Jets-Dolphins (8:30 a.m. start) : 4.9
Texans-Falcons: 4.9
Fever-Lynx: 0.4
